# 8.4 Open the file romeo.txt and read it line by line. 
# For each line, split the line into a list of words using the split() method. 
# The program should build a list of words. 
# For each word on each line check to see if the word is already in the list and if not append it to the list.
# When the program completes, sort and print the resulting words in alphabetical order.

# You can download the sample data at http://www.pythonlearn.com/code/romeo.txt



fname = raw_input("Enter file name: ")  # bekérjük a fájlnevet
fh = open(fname)                        # megnyitjuk
lst = list()                            # készítünk egy listát (ebbe tesszük majd a szavakat)
for line in fh:
    for i in line.split():              # sorokat szavakra bontjuk
        if not i in lst:                # ami még nincs a listában,                        
        	lst.append(i)                 # hozzáadjuk
lst.sort()	                            # abc-be rendezzük
print lst                               # kiíratjuk
